The Safa Briefing ahead of the organisation's elective congress, ended in controversy as delegates were leaving the Sandton venue. eNCA's Hloni Mtimkulu had to fend off a Safa official from the Western Cape, as she tried to do her job in filming a disagreement between two other officials. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The SAFA briefing ahead of the organisation's elective congress ended in controversy as delegates were leaving the Sandton venue on Friday. eNCA's Hloni Mtimkulu had to fend off a SAFA official from the Western Cape as she tried to do her job in filming a disagreement between two other officials.